# HubHub-Specific Context

## Business Model:
- Platform owner/admin controls designer database access
- Clients submit projects but cannot browse full designer database
- Admin curates candidate selection and manages offers
- Revenue from commission fees (15-25%) and matching fees

## Technical Stack:
- Frontend: Next.js 14 + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS
- Backend: Supabase (PostgreSQL + Auth + Storage)
- CV Parsing: Affinda API or Resume Parser API
- Focus: PDF CV parsing + manual completion (NO LinkedIn integration)

## MVP Required Fields:
- Core Profile: title, phone, email, availability, portfolio_url, cv_file_url, professional_summary, total_experience_years
- Skills: skill_name, category, proficiency_level (1-5)
- Work History: company_name, industry
- Languages: language_name, proficiency_level (1-5)

## Database Schema:
- 16 tables with clear required vs optional field designations
- Profile completion validation with `is_profile_complete` flag
- Admin can only include designers with complete profiles in searches

## Development Phases:
- Phase 1 (Weeks 1-3): PoC Foundation - PDF parsing + manual completion + survey integration
- Phase 2 (Weeks 4-6): Core Features - Admin matching + client portal + offers
- Phase 3 (Weeks 7-8): PoC Completion - Polish + analytics + demo prep